A .gitignore file for a MERN (MongoDB, Express.js, React, Node.js) stack application should exclude files and directories that are not necessary or that should be kept private. Below is a comprehensive .gitignore file tailored for a typical MERN stack application:

```gitignore
# Node.js dependencies
node_modules/
npm-debug.log
yarn-error.log
yarn-debug.log
package-lock.json
yarn.lock

# Logs
logs
*.log
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
pnpm-debug.log*
lerna-debug.log*

# Runtime data
pids
*.pid
*.seed
*.pid.lock

# Directory for instrumented libs generated by jscoverage/JSCover
lib-cov

# Coverage directory used by tools like istanbul
coverage/
*.lcov

# Grunt intermediate storage (https://gruntjs.com/creating-plugins#storing-task-files)
.grunt

# Bower dependency directory (https://bower.io/)
bower_components/

# Sass/CSS cache
.sass-cache/
.npm/
.jspm-cache/

# IDEs and editors
.idea/
.vscode/
*.suo
*.ntvs*
*.njsproj
*.sln
*.sw?

# Serverless directories
.serverless/

# Optional npm cache directory
.npm

# Optional eslint cache
.eslintcache

# dotenv environment variables file
.env
.env.test

# Miscellaneous
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.iml
*.hbs
*.pyc
*.pyo

# Build directories
build/
dist/
out/

# Static files
public/static/

# React Native specific
.expo/
.expo-shared/

# Generated files
*.bundle.js
*.bundle.map
*.map

# Temporary files
*.tmp
*.temp

# OS specific files
*.swp
*~
*.bak
*.orig
*.rej
*.swo
*.log
*.pid

# Dependency directories
/.pnp
.pnp.js

# Parcel-bundler cache (https://parceljs.org/)
.cache/

# Next.js build output
.next/

# Nuxt.js build output
.nuxt/

# SvelteKit build / generated output
.svelte-kit/

# Strapi
/.cache/
.build/

# temporary working files for scss compiler
.sass-cache/

# dist directory
dist/
tmp/

# Nuxt.js build output
.nuxt/

# Gatsby files
.cache/
public/

# Dependencies
# package dependency folders
node_modules/
jspm_packages/
```

This file covers various common elements found in a MERN stack application, including:

- **Node.js** dependencies and logs.
- **Build and coverage directories**.
- **IDE and editor settings**.
- **Environment variables** files.
- **OS specific files**.
- **Front-end frameworks/build tools** like React, Next.js, Gatsby, etc.

You can customize this list further based on any additional tools or directories specific to your project.